[
  {
    "id": "blk_001",
    "page_id": "pg_thompson_expert",
    "parent_block_id": "",
    "type": "heading_2",
    "text": "Opposing forensic methodology - admissibility pressure-test",
    "order": "1",
    "created_time": "2026-10-16T11:00:00Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-10-16T11:00:00Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "blk_002",
    "page_id": "pg_thompson_expert",
    "parent_block_id": "",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "The opposing side leans on a contested analytical protocol for the toxicology findings. Whether the methodology holds up at the admissibility stage is the hinge on whether we move on the suppression motion at all.",
    "order": "2",
    "created_time": "2026-10-16T11:00:00Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-10-16T11:00:00Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "blk_003",
    "page_id": "pg_thompson_expert",
    "parent_block_id": "",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Literature read so far is thin and split. One validation study defends the protocol's reliability; a separate critique flags inadequate blank-sample controls but draws on a small sample and has not been replicated. No consensus error figure is established. The question is unsettled.",
    "order": "3",
    "created_time": "2026-10-16T11:00:00Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-10-16T11:00:00Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "blk_004",
    "page_id": "pg_thompson_expert",
    "parent_block_id": "",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Conclusion stays open until the science is solid. Do not state a finding we cannot defend, and do not move on the motion or let anything go out as final while the methodology question is unresolved.",
    "order": "4",
    "created_time": "2026-10-16T11:00:00Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-10-16T11:00:00Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "blk_005",
    "page_id": "pg_delacroix_disc",
    "parent_block_id": "",
    "type": "heading_2",
    "text": "Wiretap-transcript discovery summary - DRAFT, not court-ready",
    "order": "1",
    "created_time": "2026-10-16T13:00:00Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-10-16T13:00:00Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "blk_006",
    "page_id": "pg_delacroix_disc",
    "parent_block_id": "",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Draft narrative summary of the wiretap line-sheets, to be reconciled against the raw intake index and the review tracker. Status: outstanding, citations not reconciled. Hold - do not file or send to the court until the index reconciles clean.",
    "order": "2",
    "created_time": "2026-10-16T13:00:00Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-10-16T13:00:00Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "blk_008",
    "page_id": "pg_delacroix_disc",
    "parent_block_id": "",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Sessions S01 through S20 summarised. Calls CALL-0003, CALL-0019, CALL-0044, CALL-0061, CALL-0088, CALL-0112, CALL-0150, CALL-0177 carry the substantive exchanges relied on in the narrative. Each is transcribed and reviewed.",
    "order": "3",
    "created_time": "2026-10-16T13:00:00Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-10-16T13:00:00Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "blk_009",
    "page_id": "pg_delacroix_disc",
    "parent_block_id": "",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Narrative additionally relies on CALL-0206 for the corroborating exchange on the later session. (Note for reconciliation: this citation has not been matched back to an intake row.)",
    "order": "4",
    "created_time": "2026-10-16T13:00:00Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-10-16T13:00:00Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "blk_010",
    "page_id": "pg_delacroix_disc",
    "parent_block_id": "",
    "type": "heading_2",
    "text": "Proposed exhibit list for filing",
    "order": "5",
    "created_time": "2026-10-16T13:00:00Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-10-16T13:00:00Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "blk_011",
    "page_id": "pg_delacroix_disc",
    "parent_block_id": "",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Exhibits proposed: EX-009, EX-018, EX-099, EX-022. EX-099 corresponds to CALL-0193. (Reconciliation flag: CALL-0193 is not marked verified in the tracker.)",
    "order": "6",
    "created_time": "2026-10-16T13:00:00Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-10-16T13:00:00Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "blk_012",
    "page_id": "pg_delacroix_disc",
    "parent_block_id": "",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Devon note, 16 Oct 13:40: we are clear on transcripts now - the summary is clean for review and reconciles to the index, nothing outstanding on the wiretap side.",
    "order": "7",
    "created_time": "2026-10-16T13:40:00Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-10-16T13:40:00Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "blk_013",
    "page_id": "pg_delacroix_disc",
    "parent_block_id": "",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Devon note, 16 Oct 13:05 (earlier, same day): still outstanding - two sessions not yet reconciled against the index, holding before anything goes to the court.",
